Maedi-visna, Norway
-------------------
Information received on [and dated] 11 Jul 2019 from Dre Kristina Landsverk, chief veterinary officer, Norwegian Food Safety Authority, Brumunddal, Norway

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 20 Jun 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 10 Jul 2019
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2009
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: Maedi-visna virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Steinkjer, Innherred and Fosen department, Central Region, Nord-Trondelag
Date of start of the outbreak: 20 Jun 2019
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Sheep / 220 / 4 / - / 2 / -

